<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-16T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/867: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-16T18:00:00+09:00">September 16, 1937—6
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 16—7:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>378. Following telegram has been sent to Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“September 16, 5 p.m. Your 703, September 14, 3 p.m., to the
                                        Department.<note n="35" xml:id="d369fn35">Not
                                        printed.</note> Evacuation from Mokanshan. Following
                                    memorandum has been received today from the Foreign Office:
                                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>‘The Imperial Government has completed necessary
                                            arrangements to safeguard about 150 American nationals
                                            now at Mokanshan near Hangchow, Chekiang Province, who
                                            will leave overland for Ningpo on September 22 and are
                                            due to arrive at Shanghai on September 23 on the British
                                            steamer <hi rend="italic">Hsin Peking</hi>’.</p>
                                    </quote></p>
                                <p>Repeated to Department.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>